    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-12-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="448"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/12–1746</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Acting Associate Chief of the Division of
                        Japanese and Korean Economic Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to Mr. <persName type="to">Joseph A.
                            Frank</persName>, of the Office of the Assistant Secretary of State for
                        Occupied Areas</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-17">December 17,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Pursuant to our conversation today, attached are copies of <gloss
                        target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss>–084/1 and <gloss target="#t_FEC1"
                        >FEC</gloss>–084/3.<note n="57" xml:id="d448fn1">Not attached to file copy
                        of this document.</note> The former (<gloss target="#t_FEC1"
                    >FEC</gloss>–084/1) is basically the U.S. position on Industrial Disarmament of
                    Japan (originally <gloss target="#t_SWNCC1">SWNCC</gloss> 302) as amended in
                        <gloss target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss> negotiations to date, which amendments
                    have been agreed to by the U.S. after clearance with <gloss target="#t_AH1"
                        >A–H</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_SWNCC1">SWNCC</gloss>. The latter (<gloss
                        target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss>–084/3) contains two new Chinese proposed
                    additions to the selected list of “War supporting industries” contained in
                        <gloss target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss>–084/1, viz., the addition of the <hi
                        rend="italic">heavy mechanical equipment industry</hi>, and the addition of
                    the <hi rend="italic">optical and precision instruments industry</hi>.</p>
            </div>
